for dinner, Detective?

564
00:35:59,414 --> 00:36:02,751
Oh, that's-that's so kind. I...

565
00:36:02,793 --> 00:36:03,919
Sure. Of course.

566
00:36:04,002 --> 00:36:05,128
[Elizabeth]
Uh, there's, uh, rum punch

567
00:36:05,212 --> 00:36:06,296
on the back porch.

568
00:36:06,380 --> 00:36:08,674
Adam, take Detective Costello
and Charlie

569
00:36:08,715 --> 00:36:10,050
and offer them some.

570
00:36:10,092 --> 00:36:11,718
-Uh, yeah.
-Yeah.

571
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:13,095
Come on.

572
00:36:13,178 --> 00:36:16,890
Think I'm gonna need something
a little heavier than the punch.

573
00:36:17,808 --> 00:36:18,975
[door opens]

574
00:36:19,017 --> 00:36:21,269
-Nancy, how you been?
-Oh, you know, I'm doing okay.

575
00:36:21,311 --> 00:36:23,772
Adam was suspended from school.

576
00:36:23,814 --> 00:36:26,066
-What?
-Three days home.

577
00:36:26,108 --> 00:36:28,193
I'll be making sure
it doesn't go on his record.

578
00:36:28,276 --> 00:36:30,362
No, wait, wait.
What happened?

579
00:36:30,404 --> 00:36:33,824
He and Wesley got into a fight.

580
00:36:33,865 --> 00:36:35,158
You're kidding.

581
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:37,202
No, I-I dropped everything,

582
00:36:37,285 --> 00:36:38,453
brought him home,
cooked for him,

583
00:36:38,495 --> 00:36:40,122
paid attention
to what he was saying

584
00:36:40,205 --> 00:36:42,165
-and not saying any...
-You're a saint, Elizabeth.

585
00:36:42,249 --> 00:36:44,251
-Got it.
-Yeah.

586
00:36:44,334 --> 00:36:47,295
-Why didn't he call me?
-Yeah, wh-why do you think

587
00:36:47,379 --> 00:36:49,256
-he didn't call you?
-I don't know.

588
00:36:49,339 --> 00:36:51,925
-Why don't you know?
-Oh, Jesus Christ. Really?

589
00:36:51,967 --> 00:36:54,970
A fight with Wesley?

590
00:36:55,011 --> 00:36:56,722
I-I mean...

591
00:36:56,805 --> 00:36:59,099
Did he-did he say why?

592
00:36:59,141 --> 00:37:00,142
Yes and no.

593
00:37:00,225 --> 00:37:01,643
What the hell does that mean?

594
00:37:01,685 --> 00:37:05,397
Well, on the surface, uh,
an argument about photography.

595
00:37:05,439 --> 00:37:10,026
Underneath, a child boiling up
with a lot of pain and anger.

596
00:37:10,110 --> 00:37:12,529
-[phone ringing]
-[groans] You see?

597
00:37:12,571 --> 00:37:14,573
Bang, in the middle
of a conversation about

598
00:37:14,614 --> 00:37:16,992
your son's suspension
from school for violence,

599
00:37:17,075 --> 00:37:18,285
and you really
want to take that call?

600
00:37:18,368 --> 00:37:19,870
Let me ask you again.
Why do you think

601
00:37:19,911 --> 00:37:22,372
he didn't call you?

602
00:37:23,915 --> 00:37:26,418
I d-I don't...

603
00:37:27,043 --> 00:37:29,963
What-what did...
what did you and-and...

604
00:37:30,046 --> 00:37:33,341
Detective Costello talk about?
Hmm?

605
00:37:33,383 --> 00:37:35,927
[crickets chirping outside]

606
00:37:37,012 --> 00:37:39,264
I was disappointed
you didn't call.

607
00:37:39,306 --> 00:37:41,099
On the anniversary.

608
00:37:41,183 --> 00:37:42,392
But you didn't, so...

